Peachtree Investment Advisors Inc. Has $1,577,000 Stake in Dover Corporation (NYSE:DOV)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments




Peachtree Investment Advisors Inc. maintained its position in shares of  Dover Corporation (NYSE:DOV) during the second quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor  owned 19,655 shares of the industrial products company’s stock at the end of the second quarter. Dover Corporation makes up   1.4% of Peachtree Investment Advisors Inc.’s investment portfolio, making the stock its 22nd largest position. Peachtree Investment Advisors Inc.’s holdings in Dover Corporation were worth $1,577,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other hedge funds have also added to or reduced their stakes in the company. National Pension Service increased its stake in shares of  Dover Corporation by 0.8% in the first quarter. National Pension Service now owns 145,970 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $11,688,000 after buying an additional 1,220 shares during the last quarter.  Gulf International Bank UK Ltd boosted its stake in  Dover Corporation by 1.7% in the first quarter. Gulf International Bank UK Ltd now owns 48,908 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $3,929,000 after buying an additional 800 shares during the last quarter.  Contravisory Investment Management Inc. boosted its stake in  Dover Corporation by 7,073.9% in the first quarter. Contravisory Investment Management Inc. now owns 3,300 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $265,000 after buying an additional 3,254 shares during the last quarter.  Chevy Chase Trust Holdings Inc. boosted its stake in  Dover Corporation by 3.1% in the first quarter. Chevy Chase Trust Holdings Inc. now owns 140,055 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $11,253,000 after buying an additional 4,217 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Macquarie Group Ltd. boosted its stake in  Dover Corporation by 2.6% in the fourth quarter. Macquarie Group Ltd. now owns 3,900 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $292,000 after buying an additional 100 shares during the last quarter. 84.62% of the stock is currently owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Dover Corporation alerts:



Dover Corporation (NYSE DOV) traded down 0.36% on Friday, reaching $82.87. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 1,185,977 shares. The firm’s 50 day moving average price is $82.08 and its 200-day moving average price is $80.17. Dover Corporation has a 52 week low of $65.50 and a 52 week high of $85.31. The company has a market capitalization of $12.90 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 22.40 and a beta of 1.27. 





Dover Corporation (NYSE:DOV) last posted its earnings results on Thursday, July 20th. The industrial products company reported $1.04 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $1.01 by $0.03. The company had revenue of $1.99 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.94 billion. Dover Corporation had a return on equity of 13.56% and a net margin of 8.61%. The business’s revenue was up 18.2% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period last year, the company earned $0.76 earnings per share.  On average, equities analysts predict that  Dover Corporation will post $4.27 EPS for the current year. 
