						Peachtree Investment Advisors Inc. Has $1,577,000 Stake in Dover Corporation (DOV)					

						 July 12th, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Tyrone Williams 


							Filed Under: Finance - SEC Filing Articles 







Tweet










Peachtree Investment Advisors Inc. continued to hold its position in shares of  Dover Corporation (NYSE:DOV) during the second quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The institutional investor  owned 19,655 shares of the industrial products company’s stock at the end of the second quarter. Dover Corporation makes up   1.4% of Peachtree Investment Advisors Inc.’s investment portfolio, making the stock its 22nd largest position. Peachtree Investment Advisors Inc.’s holdings in Dover Corporation were worth $1,577,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also made changes to their positions in the company. Pennsylvania Trust Co increased its position in shares of  Dover Corporation by 88.5% in the second quarter. Pennsylvania Trust Co now owns 8,877 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $712,000 after buying an additional 4,167 shares in the last quarter.  Gateway Investment Advisers LLC increased its position in shares of  Dover Corporation by 2.3% in the second quarter. Gateway Investment Advisers LLC now owns 10,577 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $848,000 after buying an additional 234 shares in the last quarter.  Iberiabank Corp increased its position in shares of  Dover Corporation by 0.3% in the second quarter. Iberiabank Corp now owns 36,376 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $2,918,000 after buying an additional 122 shares in the last quarter.  Xact Kapitalforvaltning AB increased its position in shares of  Dover Corporation by 73.7% in the second quarter. Xact Kapitalforvaltning AB now owns 35,196 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $2,823,000 after buying an additional 14,931 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, DnB Asset Management AS increased its position in shares of  Dover Corporation by 3.0% in the second quarter. DnB Asset Management AS now owns 23,916 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $1,919,000 after buying an additional 700 shares in the last quarter. 84.65% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 
Dover Corporation (DOV) traded up 1.352% on Wednesday, reaching $84.335. The company had a trading volume of 519,317 shares. Dover Corporation has a one year low of $65.50 and a one year high of $84.66. The company’s 50 day moving average is $81.54 and its 200-day moving average is $79.42. The firm has a market capitalization of $13.13 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 22.793 and a beta of 1.27. 




Dover Corporation (NYSE:DOV) last released its earnings results on Thursday, April 20th. The industrial products company reported $1.09 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.61 by $0.48. Dover Corporation had a net margin of 8.33% and a return on equity of 12.93%. The firm had revenue of $1.81 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.77 billion. During the same period last year, the business earned $0.64 earnings per share. The business’s revenue was up 11.8% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, equities research analysts expect that  Dover Corporation will post $4.20 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The business also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Thursday, June 15th. Shareholders of record on Wednesday, May 31st were paid a dividend of $0.44 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend  was Friday, May 26th. This represents a $1.76 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 2.12%. Dover Corporation’s dividend payout ratio  is presently 47.44%. 
